B.Kf=new A.b5("tm_identity","TM: Accept All (Trivial)","Build the simplest possible Turing machine: one that accepts every input by halting immediately.\nA single state that is both start and accept will do it. TM transition format: readSymbol writeSymbol Direction (e.g. aBR = read a, write B, move Right).","      tm mode\n      n0 = A\n      A = (600.0, 360.0)\n      A is accepted\n      to A angle = -1.0000, 0.0000\n    ",B.aG,B.TJ,0.25,"tm")
B.U1=new A.cr("tm_identity")
B.K_=new A.b5("tm_reject_all","TM: Reject All","Build a TM that loops forever on any non-empty input (rejects by non-halt) and accepts only the empty tape.\nHint: a start state with a self-loop on every symbol that moves right will spin forever.","      tm mode\n      n0 = A\n      n1 = B\n      A = (480.0, 360.0)\n      B = (820.0, 360.0)\n      B is accepted\n      A to B = \u2205\u2205S\n      to A angle = -1.0000, 0.0000\n    ",B.aG,B.U1,0.5,"tm")
B.U2=new A.cr("tm_reject_all")
B.Ka=new A.b5("tm_unary_increment","TM: Unary Increment","Build a TM over {1} that accepts strings of the form 1\u207f for any n \u2265 0. The machine should scan past all 1s and accept when it hits blank. This checks you can drive the head right and accept on blank.","      tm mode\n      n0 = A\n      n1 = B\n      A = (460.0, 360.0)\n      B = (820.0, 360.0)\n      B is accepted\n      A to A = 11R\n      A to B = \u2205\u2205S\n      l0(11R) loop angle = -1.5708\n      to A angle = -1.0000, 0.0000\n    ",B.aG,B.U2,0.75,"tm")
B.Bg=new A.cr("tm_unary_increment")
B.Ki=new A.b5("tm_anbn","TM: a\u207fb\u207f","Build a TM that accepts exactly strings of the form a\u207fb\u207f (n \u2265 1). Classic TM exercise: repeatedly cross off one a and one b until both sides are exhausted.","      tm mode\n      n0 = A\n      n1 = B\n      n2 = C\n      n3 = D\n      n4 = E\n      A = (260.0, 200.0)\n      B = (660.0, 200.0)\n      C = (1060.0, 200.0)\n      D = (660.0, 560.0)\n      E = (260.0, 560.0)\n      E is accepted\n      A to B = aXR\n      B to B = aXR\n      B to C = bXL\n      C to D = XXL\n      D to D = aXL\n      D to A = XXR\n      A to E = \u2205\u2205S\n      l1(aXR) loop angle = -1.5708\n      l3(XXL) loop angle = -1.5708\n      l4(aXL) loop angle = 1.5708\n      aXR curve = 80.0\n      bXL curve = 80.0\n      XXR curve = 80.0\n      to A angle = -1.0000, 0.0000\n    ",B.aG,B.Bg,0.2,"tm")
B.Bf=new A.cr("tm_anbn")
B.Ju=new A.b5("tm_binary_increment","TM: Binary Increment","Build a TM over {0,1} that accepts any binary string (treat the tape as a binary number and verify the head can scan it). The machine must scan from left to right over 0s and 1s and halt-accept on blank.","      tm mode\n      n0 = A\n      n1 = B\n      A = (480.0, 360.0)\n      B = (820.0, 360.0)\n      B is accepted\n      A to A = 00R\n      A to A = 11R\n      A to B = \u2205\u2205S\n      l0(00R) loop angle = -1.5708\n      l1(11R) loop angle = -0.8000\n      to A angle = -1.0000, 0.0000\n    ",B.aG,B.Bf,0.45,"tm")
B.JL=new A.b5("tm_unary_addition","TM: Unary Addition","Build a TM over {1, +} that accepts any string of the form 1\u207f+1\u1d50 (unary numbers separated by a plus sign).\nThe machine should scan past all 1s and the + symbol and halt-accept on blank.","      tm mode\n      n0 = A\n      n1 = B\n      A = (480.0, 360.0)\n      B = (840.0, 360.0)\n      B is accepted\n      A to A = 11R\n      A to A = ++R\n      A to B = \u2205\u2205S\n      l0(11R) loop angle = -1.5708\n      l1(++R) loop angle = -0.8000\n      to A angle = -1.0000, 0.0000\n    ",B.aG,B.Bg,0.7,"tm")
